titles: An answer to Mr. Molyneux his Case of Ireland's being bound by acts of Parliament in England, stated, and his dangerous notion of Ireland's being under no subordination to the parliamentary authority of England refuted, by reasoning from his own arguments and authorities.
author: Cary, John, d. 1720?, attributed name.
Atwood, William, d. 1705?, attributed name.
notes: Sometimes attributed to William Atwood and/or John Cary, each of whom published similar works in 1698.
